results.name: Irregular triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of connected graphs on n unlabeled nodes with domination number k, n >= 1, 1 <= k <= A065033(n+1).
comment: Bivariate inverse Euler transform of A263284. This sequence can be derived from A263284 because the domination number of a disconnected graph is the sum of the domination numbers of its components.
Connected graphs with greatest domination number include the path graph.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Domination Number
